<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">AMC</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nothing in this newsletter is ever investment =
advice. For instance, yesterday AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc. announced t=
hat it had completed its $250 million at-the-market stock offering just as =
a meme-stock rally was getting started, and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/35389736.258338/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvb=
S9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMTQvYW1jLWlzLWJhY2stdG9vP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1=
MTUyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV=
0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDUxNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB0c63cfc4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">I wrote</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If I were an AMC investor, I suppo=
se I would find it bullish that AMC (1) was selling a bunch of stock into t=
he market and (2) stopped. There is a good technical reason for AMC investo=
rs to be happy: There is less supply coming. When AMC=E2=80=99s stock ralli=
ed hard on Monday, AMC was selling into the demand. If AMC rallies today, A=
MC will not be selling into the demand.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well, if I were an AMC investor, I would have =
been wrong! AMC=E2=80=99s stock did rally yesterday =E2=80=94=C2=A0or, rath=
er, it opened up more than 100%=C2=A0from Monday=E2=80=99s close, and then =
gave back a lot of those gains over the course of the day =E2=80=94=C2=A0an=
d AMC=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>sell into the demand. Bloomberg=E2=80=99s <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35389736.258338/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMTUvYW1jLXNlaXplc=
y1vbi1tZW1lLXN0b2NrLW1vbWVudHVtLXRvLWN1dC0xNjQtbWlsbGxpb24tb2YtZGVidD9jbXBp=
ZD1CQkQwNTE1MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2x=
ldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA1MTUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cBeae4b455" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">
Claire Boston reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">AMC Entertainment Holdings is taking advantage=
 of its meme stock rally to reduce its debt, revisiting a playbook that hel=
ped it shore up liquidity in 2021.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The movie theater chain said in a regulatory f=
iling that it reached a private deal to swap about $164 million of its 10% =
notes due 2026 for 23.3 million shares of newly-issued stock. Based on the =
principal exchanged and accrued interest, the new stock had a value of $7.3=
3 per share. AMC shares closed on Tuesday at $6.85.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">AMC, much of whose debt trades at distressed p=
rices, has been chipping away at its maturities through other swaps and buy=
backs. It exchanged around $200 million of the debt for shares last year.=
=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/35389736.258338/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0Fy=
Y2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMDAwMTQxMTU3OS8wMDAxMTA0NjU5MjQwNjE1NTAvdG0yNDE0NTU=
yZDFfOGsuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa939a841" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the filing</a>, wh=
ich says that AMC got rid of $164 million of =E2=80=9C10%/12% Cash/PIK Togg=
le Second Lien Subordinated Notes due 2026,=E2=80=9D which is just the sort=
 of name that tells you it trades at distressed prices. (Bloomberg tells me=
 they were trading at around 70 cents on the dollar last week, and rallied =
to about 85 yesterday.) The deal was at an =E2=80=9Cimplied value=E2=80=9D =
of $7.33 per share, says AMC, though that seems to be based on an =E2=80=9C=
implied value=E2=80=9D for the bonds of 100 cents on the dollar. If you val=
ue the bonds at 85, then the implied stock value is about $6.27.<a class=3D=
"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !imp=
ortant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fun question is: What is the=C2=A0<em>timi=
ng=C2=A0</em>of this trade? You can imagine two approaches:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Hedge funds with $164 million of AMC =
bonds called up AMC and said =E2=80=9Chey can we swap these for stock?=E2=
=80=9D AMC said=C2=A0=E2=80=9Csure,=E2=80=9D and they negotiated a price of=
 $7.33 per share. This negotiation presumably happened at some point yester=
day, when AMC=E2=80=99s stock ranged from a low of $5.85 to a high of $11.8=
8, with a volume-weighted average price of $8.64. The hedge funds got the s=
tock at some point yesterday and then had to sell it, like, yesterday after=
noon or today.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgroun=
d-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a> As of noon today, AMC=E2=80=99s stock has ranged from a low of $4.71 t=
o a high of $6.60, so if they were=C2=A0selling today the hedge funds did n=
ot get anywhere close to $7.33. Even if they were selling yesterday afterno=
on, the stock spent a lot of time below $7.33.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">Hedge funds with $164 million of AMC bonds=C2=A0<em>shorted </=
em>$164 million of AMC stock yesterday<em>=C2=A0</em>and=C2=A0<em>then=C2=
=A0</em>called up AMC to say =E2=80=9Chey can we swap these for stock?=E2=
=80=9D AMC said =E2=80=9Csure,=E2=80=9D and the hedge funds were like =E2=
=80=9Cgreat we got our short off at eight bucks so can we do $7.33?=E2=80=
=9D And for AMC, selling $170 million of stock at $7.33 yesterday =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0after selling $250 million over the past six weeks <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35389736.258338/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Vj=
Lmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMDAwMTQxMTU3OS8wMDAxMTA0NjU5MjQ=
wNjA4MTMvdG0yNDEyNzk5ZDJfOGsuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC6e3b46a0" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">at $3.45</a> =E2=80=94 is pure windfall.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For the bondholders, the second trade =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0sell stock first, acquire it later =E2=80=94=C2=A0is clearly bette=
r than the first; it was better to sell into the beginning of yesterday=E2=
=80=99s AMC rally than to wait until it lost steam. I mean! It=E2=80=99s cl=
early better in hindsight! There have been some mornings when shorting AMC =
into an inexplicable rally would have been a terrible idea.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For AMC, the lesson is =E2=80=9Cas far as poss=
ible, do all of your financing in meme-stock-rally windows.=E2=80=9D I supp=
ose it=E2=80=99s hard to predict those, though, even for AMC.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway this week=E2=80=99s=C2=A0meme rally <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35389736.258338/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMTUvZ2FtZXN0b3At=
YW1jLXN1cmdlLWFzLW1lbWUtc3RvY2stcmFsbHktZXh0ZW5kcy10by10aGlyZC1kYXk_Y21waWQ=
9QkJEMDUxNTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZX=
R0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNTE1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB06870534" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">is already fizzling</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The meme rally that added about $11 billion in=
 value to GameStop Corp. and AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc. faltered Wedne=
sday, wiping out a large swath of the gains in the first minutes of trading=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">GameStop fell as much as 33% on Wednesday, the=
 most intraday since March 2021. AMC sank as much as 26% after the beleague=
red movie theater chain took advantage of its equity rally through a privat=
e deal to reduce its debt. The stocks had more than doubled over the first =
two days of the week, before the Wednesday slide erased more than $4 billio=
n in market value between the two.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The latest rout brings further echoes of the m=
eme insanity that gripped markets in early 2021. Then, GameStop soared by m=
ore than 1000% in a matter of weeks before rapidly unwinding much of the ga=
ins. The stock swung for months, never fully regaining its early heights, b=
efore the retail mania finally dissipated.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know. On the one hand, it woul=
d be weird to have a months-long, 1,000%, massive-cultural-phenomenon meme-=
stock rally every few years. On the other hand, it=E2=80=99s not=C2=A0<em>n=
ot=C2=A0</em>weird to have a days-long, 100%, =E2=80=9Coh this again huh?=
=E2=80=9D meme-stock rally every few years. The 2021 meme-stock rally was m=
ostly divorced from corporate fundamentals, but it was connected to=C2=A0<e=
m>something</em>; there really was a cultural phenomenon. The 2024 one does=
n=E2=80=99t even have that.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/35389736.258338/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZ=
