reet <em>could</em> describe the trade secret, Jane Street, now a month lat=
er, still refuses to do so. Jane Street=E2=80=99s persistent refusal to ide=
ntify the supposed trade secret leads to only one conclusion=E2=80=94Jane S=
treet cannot identify any trade secret that Schadewald and Spottiswood alle=
gedly misappropriated.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At some level, noticing things like =E2=80=9Cw=
ow options in India are systematically mispriced=E2=80=9D really is the bus=
iness of a trading firm like Jane Street, and it does invest a lot of time =
and resources into hiring and training people so that they will notice thos=
e things. But once you have noticed them, it=E2=80=99s hard to argue that J=
ane Street=C2=A0<em>owns=C2=A0</em>that mispricing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Instead, Schadewald and Spottiswood=C2=A0argue=
, Jane Street is using this lawsuit to deter its=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</em>e=
mployees from leaving, by sending a message that if they leave for a compet=
itor they=E2=80=99ll be sued for stealing trade secrets. They point to some=
 timing issues here. When Jane Street originally sued, it asked the judge t=
o temporarily stop Millennium from trading the=C2=A0Indian options strategy=
 until they could have a trial on whether it was stolen. The judge declined=
 to do that, but agreed to hold a=C2=A0trial quickly to decide=C2=A0whether=
=C2=A0to ban Millennium from trading it. But then Jane Street withdrew its =
request for an injunction: Instead of having a quick trial on whether or no=
t to stop Millennium from trading the strategy, they can have a more leisur=
ely trial on whether Millennium stole the strategy and, if it did, what dam=
ages it should pay. The traders argue:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Jane Street=E2=80=99s delay is tel=
ling. The objectives of chilling competition in the markets Schadewald and =
Spottiswood trade in, chilling competition among firms for skilled employee=
s, and sending a message to high-skilled employees that departures to a com=
petitor will be met with legal action even in the absence of any noncompete=
 agreement=E2=80=94are better served by leaving a pending lawsuit hanging o=
ver Schadewald and Spottiswood=E2=80=99s head than by holding a trial that =
will fully and finally adjudicate the claims against Schadewald and Spottis=
wood. Jane Street=E2=80=99s claims against Schadewald and Spottiswood=E2=80=
=94based on a nonexistent trade secret and irresponsible and unfounded alle=
gations of misappropriation=E2=80=94are quintessential bad faith.</p></bloc=
kquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is probably true that Jane Street benefits =
from uncertainty here. If you are a Jane Street trader and you know (1) exa=
ctly what sort of intellectual property Jane Street is mad at=C2=A0Schadewa=
ld and Spottiswood for taking and (2) whether or not a court thinks they we=
re allowed to take it, you can make pretty well-informed decisions about wh=
at sorts of ideas=C2=A0<em>you=C2=A0</em>could potentially take to a compet=
itor. But if the strategy is redacted and the trial is delayed, then it=E2=
=80=99s at least=C2=A0<em>possible=C2=A0</em>that general ideas like =E2=80=
=9Ctrade options in India=E2=80=9D will get you in trouble, and you=E2=80=
=99ll be more nervous about leaving.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By the way, the traders=E2=80=99 reply, like J=
ane Street=E2=80=99s complaint, is pretty redacted, though the bits about I=
ndian options trading are prominent and unredacted. But it gives some hints=
 about Jane Street=E2=80=99s culture. For instance, here=E2=80=99s paragrap=
h 23 of their counterclaims:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Schadewald and Spottiswood had sig=
nificant success while employed by Jane Street. They and the teams they led=
 generated profits of approximately <strong>[redacted]</strong> for Jane St=
reet. In December 2022, <strong>[redacted]</strong>. When Schadewald depart=
ed, Jane Street=E2=80=99s <em>de facto</em> CEO texted Schadewald to tell h=
im that =E2=80=9Cyour impact on the firm was huge and I don=E2=80=99t know =
how we can fill the gap left.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously one would want to know the profits. =
But it is also kind of fun that Jane Street is a sort of Wall Street social=
ist collective without a chief executive officer =E2=80=94=C2=A0there=E2=80=
=99s a =E2=80=9Cde facto CEO,=E2=80=9D but no one with that actual title. E=
lsewhere in socialist collectives:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">2023 was the most successful year =
of Schadewald=E2=80=99s and Spottiswood=E2=80=99s careers at Jane Street. B=
ut Jane Street, as a business philosophy,=C2=A0<strong>[redacted]</strong>.=
 Schadewald and Spottiswood were naturally disappointed with Jane Street=E2=
=80=99s compensation decisions delivered during their 2023 year-end perform=
ance reviews and felt that they were not given a clear path to advancement =
within Jane Street and that their contributions to the firm were being unde=
rvalued.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CJane Street, as a business philosophy=
,=E2=80=9D did something, but what?=C2=A0Presumably =E2=80=9Cdidn=E2=80=99t=
 pay them as much as they were worth on the open market,=E2=80=9D but for p=
hilosophical reasons.=C2=A0</p>
